The encounter coincided with heightened political tensions between Canada and the U.S., symbolizing resistance.
title: American Bald eagle vs Canada Goose: 'Symbolic' wildlife clash captured

description: South Africa's David Miller criticised the logistical disruptions that required his team to make a quick round-trip to Dubai before their Champions Trophy semi-final defeat against New Zealand. The scheduling issue arose due to India's refusal to play in Pakistan, resulting in South Africa and Australia having to travel to Dubai. New Zealand will face India in the final.
title: 'Not ideal': David Miller on travel to Dubai during Champions Trophy

description: Samajwadi Party MLA Abu Azmi was suspended for the entire Maharashtra budget session over his remarks on Aurangzeb. Azmi called the decision arbitrary, expressing concerns for his family's safety. Despite willing to retract his statement, protests continued with SP's Akhilesh Yadav and Sena UBT's Uddhav Thackeray sharing strong opinions.
title: 'Threat to my life and that of my family': Abu Azmi calls suspension arbitrary

description: US President Trump made 13-year-old cancer patient Devarjaye 'DJ' Daniel an honorary Secret Service agent, marking history. During his address to Congress, Trump arranged for Daniel's induction, fulfilling his law enforcement dream. DJ, battling brain cancer, shared a moving reflection, inspiring many with his strength and perseverance despite his terminal illness.
title: Watch: 13-yr-old cancer fighter gives Trump 'big hug' after joining secret services

description: US Defence Secretary Pete Hegseth stated that the US is prepared for conflict with China amid escalating trade tensions. Tensions rose after President Trump doubled tariffs on Chinese imports, prompting China to respond with its own tariffs. Hegseth underscored the importance of military strength, while emphasizing Trump's positive relationship with President Xi Jinping and prioritizing Indo-Pacific military readiness.
title: 'We're prepared': US on China's 'ready for any type of war' statement

description: China announced a 7.2% hike in its defence budget, bringing it to over $245 billion, reflecting its continued military modernization. This intensifies strategic challenges for the US and India, particularly in the Indo-Pacific region, amid mounting geopolitical tensions. On the other hand, India's defence budget remains constrained by operational shortfalls and spending limitations.
title: 3x higher than India: At $245 billion, China hikes defence budget by 7.2%

description: Kane Williamson stresses the importance of learning from New Zealand's earlier defeat to India as they prepare for the Champions Trophy final against the same opponents in Dubai on March 9. New Zealand advanced after a 50-run win over South Africa with standout performances from Williamson, Rachin Ravindra and Mitchell Santner.
title: 'Anything can happen': Williamson on CT final vs India

description: Top stock market recommendations: Aakash K Hindocha from Nuvama suggests buying Indigo, Jindal Steel, and Medanta. Nifty shows signs of recovery after 10 days of decline with support, while Bank Nifty also indicates potential upside.
title: Buy calls for today: Stock recommendations for today

description: Tamil Nadu chief minister MK Stalin once again criticizes the BJP-led central government over its language policies in the National Education Policy 2020. Stalin accuses BJP leaders of treating Tamil Nadu as second-class citizens and questions their commitment to the Tamil language, demanding linguistic equality and the removal of Hindi imposition.
title: 'Chauvinist, anti-nationals are Hindi zealots': TN CM Stalin's fresh attack on NEP

description: In Nuh, 34 people were arrested for taking the Class X Haryana exams on behalf of others, with most motivated by personal relationships. Strict measures, including police presence and physical barriers, were implemented to curb cheating across various exam centers in the state.
title: Haryana Class X board exams: Love ke liye cheating bhi karega

description: Kannada actor Ranya Rao was intercepted at KIA with 14.2kg of gold bars concealed in a belt. Subsequent searches at her residence uncovered ₹2.1 crore worth of gold ornaments and ₹2.7 crore in cash. Investigations suggest these were linked to a prominent politician.
title: More gold worth Rs 2.1 cr, Rs 2.7 cr cash recovered from K'taka DGP's daughter's flat

description: Mumbaikars are facing intense heat as temperatures reached 37.4°C, 4.4° above the seasonal average. The India Meteorological Department (IMD) forecasts temperatures to rise further, peaking at 38°C by Sunday. The latest spike is attributed to strong easterly winds and could last through March 11.
title: Mumbai is heating up again: Temperature hits 37.4°C

description: Elon Musk has accused the Biden administration of delaying the return of Nasa astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore from the ISS, despite SpaceX's offer for a rescue mission. The astronauts have been stranded due to Nasa deeming Boeing’s Starliner unsafe for re-entry. They are now scheduled to return on a SpaceX Crew Dragon in March.
title: Musk accuses Biden of blocking SpaceX mission to bring Sunita Williams home

description: President Donald Trump issued a final warning to Hamas, demanding the immediate release of American hostages in Gaza. This follows his meeting with former hostages and signals the US's direct engagement with Hamas representatives in Qatar, breaking from longstanding US policy.
title: 'There will be hell': Trump gives Hamas 'last warning' to leave Gaza, release hostages
Arvind Kejriwal's Punjab visit for vipassana stirs 'luxury' row

description: Vicky Kaushal's historical drama Chhaava has achieved considerable success at the Indian box office, nearing the Rs 500 crore milestone with strong earnings over three weeks. The film saw political recognition with special screenings organized for MLAs and MLCs, and has been praised for bringing history to the younger generation.
title: 'Chhaava' collection day 20: Drama to miss Rs 500 cr mark at week 3 end

description: Boatman Pintu Mahara and his family from Prayagraj expanded their fleet in anticipation of the Maha Kumbh influx, significantly increasing their income. The family credits their financial transformation to the strategic organization of the event by PM Narendra Modi and CM Yogi Adityanath, which attracted millions of devotees.
title: Fount of prosperity at Sangam? Boatman 'earned ₹30cr in 45 days of Maha Kumbh'

description: A massive fire ignited at a dumpsite in Noida's Sector 32, fueled by dry waste and strong winds. The blaze, which started due to a discarded bidi, is being battled by 15 fire tenders and 75 firefighters. The accused, a drunken man attempting suicide, has been taken into custody.
title: Bidi leads to fire at Noida dumping yard
Education, AI, and healthcare at core of Budget vision: PM Modi
EPS hint, new Annamalai tilt stir BJP-ADMK alliance talk

description: Khalistani extremists in London heckled and attempted to attack external affairs minister S Jaishankar. The incident occurred during Jaishankar’s UK visit to strengthen the India-UK strategic partnership. Police officers present appeared unresponsive to the vandalism.
title: Khalistani extremists heckle, attempt to attack S Jaishankar in London

description: Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath attributed the pollution in the Ganga river to the British era. While addressing the Legislative Council, he mentioned that despite the pollution, the river remains sacred to the people.
title: Don't give gyan to Indians on cleaning: Yogi blames Britishers for Ganga pollution
Over 1 lakh 'dependent' Indians fear 'self-deportation' from US

description: A 27-year-old student from Rangareddy district, Gampa Praveen, was shot dead during a suspected robbery in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. Praveen was close to completing his MS in data science at the University of Wisconsin and worked part-time at a local store. His family is devastated and struggling with limited information about the incident.
title: Telangana student shot dead during robbery bid in US

description: Ahmedabad police arrested fugitive Ashok Thakor, a chain-snatcher on the run for 34 years, but face difficulties as case files are missing. Despite apprehending Thakor, who was living as a scrap dealer, there are no FIR or court documents to support the case, creating a legal challenge for the crime branch.
title: Fugitive chain-snatcher caught after 34 years, but case in limbo as police lose files

description: China announced a 7.2% hike in its defence budget, bringing it to over $245 billion, reflecting its continued military modernization. This intensifies strategic challenges for the US and India, particularly in the Indo-Pacific region, amid mounting geopolitical tensions. On the other hand, India's defence budget remains constrained by operational shortfalls and spending limitations.
title: 3x higher than India: At $245 billion, China hikes defence budget by 7.2%

description: An active terrorist of Babbar Khalsa International, Lajar Masih, was arrested by Uttar Pradesh STF and Punjab Police in Kaushambi district. Recovered items include explosives, arms, and an Aadhaar card. Masih had escaped custody in Punjab in 2024 and was linked to ISI operatives.
title: Babbar Khalsa International terrorist with ISI links held in UP
EAM S Jaishankar calls for return of 'stolen' Kashmir from Pakistan

description: India and the UK are enhancing their bilateral ties to address key international issues and boost economic cooperation. Foreign ministers discussed strategic coordination and the progress of ongoing trade talks, while also covering the Ukraine conflict, West Asia, and developments in Bangladesh and the Commonwealth.
title: India-UK ties help stabilise uncertain, volatile world: EAM S Jaishankar

description: BSP chief Mayawati removed her brother Anand Kumar from his additional role as national coordinator after he expressed reluctance due to his son Akash Anand's sacking. Mayawati appointed Jat leader Randhir Beniwal and Rajya Sabha MP Ramji Gautam as co-national coordinators, enhancing the party's leadership composition.
title: Mayawati picks Jat face for key BSP post after brother turns down offer

description: Punjab farmers' march to Chandigarh was largely restricted by police, with many being detained and later released. SKM condemned the police action and stated that more than 15,000 farmers joined the protests across the state. Meanwhile, Jagjit Singh Dallewal completed 100 days of his fast unto death, urging the central government to accept farmers' demands regarding MSP.
title: Punjab police thwart farmers' march to Chandigarh
